				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{NPV}=\sum \limits_{t=0}^T\left({B}_t-{C}_t\right){\left(1+r\right)}^{-t} $$\end{document}

The discounted payback period [year k in Eq. (6.3)] is the first period at which the summed up discounted net benefits of an investment are greater than or equal to zero, so that6.3NPVk=∑t=0kBt−Ct1+r−t≥0andNPVk−1=∑t=0k−1Bt−Ct1+r−t<0.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
