				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{MIRR}=\sqrt[T]{\frac{\sum \limits_0^T{\mathrm{NB}}_t^{\mathrm{pos}}{\left(1+\mathrm{rr}\right)}^{T-t}}{\sum \limits_0^T{\mathrm{NB}}_t^{\mathrm{neg}}{\left(1+\mathrm{rf}\right)}^{-t}}}-1. $$\end{document}

Constant annual cash flows in arrears (i.e. a constant yearly rent or an annuity NBt = Bt − Ct = constant = NB for all t = 1, …, T) can be transformed into one single present value applying the Present Value Annuity Factor (PVAF):6.7NPV=∑1TNB1+r−t=NB∑1T1+r−t=NB1+rT−1r1+rT=NB·PVAF.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
