Thus, the PVAF transforms a constant(!) yearly payment NB (to be obtained for the next T years) into one single present value. Note that t = 1, …, T and that formula (6.7) applies for payments in arrears. In the case of a perpetuity (i.e. an ‘eternal’ annuity NBt = NB with t = 1, …, ∞), the PVAF in formula (6.7) can be simplified:6.7aNPV∞=∑1∞NB1+r−t=NB∑1∞1+r−t=NB1r=NB·PVAF∞.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
